    {"parentUuid":"7364d241-51ec-4825-a069-2dcede6c086e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"fb0f202a-bbc2-45ee-b115-e70a56807d47","agentId":"acbd4bb9ebce75959","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R6v5f8mGrUKixN1VrRqcGj","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /apps/aplikacijos/prime-research/status/CLOSED_PATHS.md has been updated successfully."}]},"uuid":"4b18e8f4-1041-45d9-9137-b39a685c67b4","timestamp":"2026-04-04T21:08:41.824Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7364d241-51ec-4825-a069-2dcede6c086e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"a7d53bb6-087f-4e7d-81de-1d8a45f40cf3","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"main","slug":"sparkling-chasing-pascal"}
    {"parentUuid":"4b18e8f4-1041-45d9-9137-b39a685c67b4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"acbd4bb9ebce75959","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013eZMi1PqkYXR8i9t3NPZPk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the summary of what was done and the findings:\n\n---\n\n**Experiment completed and saved to:**\n- `/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research/experiments/algebraic/pslq_identity_search.py` -- main search script\n- `/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research/experiments/algebraic/pslq_crossvalidation.py` -- cross-validation script\n- `/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research/experiments/algebraic/pslq_identity_results.txt` -- full results with analysis\n\n**What was tested (f(x) = pi(x) - R(x), x = 2..10000):**\n\n1. **Linear PSLQ relations** at 7 x-values against 12 basis functions (log, sqrt, x^{1/k}, li variants, sin/cos of gamma_1*log(x)). Found relations at x=200,500,2000,5000 with residuals ~10^{-37}.\n\n2. **Polynomial relations** (degree 2,3,4) at 4 x-values against sqrt(x), x^{1/3}, log(x). Found relations at x=500,5000.\n\n3. **Recurrence relations** (orders 2-10, plus augmented). Best rms = 0.309 (order 10), relative rms ~18% -- essentially no predictive power.\n\n4. **Modular identities** -- round(f(x)) mod m is non-uniform (reflecting f's bounded range ~[-5.5, 5.6]), frac(f(x)) is uniform. No dependence on x mod 2,3,5.\n\n5. **Functional equations** -- f(xy) vs f(x): correlations ~ -0.6 to -0.8, rms ~ 1.5. No useful relation.\n\n6. **Discrete derivative** -- Df(x) = [x+1 prime] - DR(x) exactly (by definition, residual ~10^{-17}). No PSLQ relation on Df beyond this tautology.\n\n7. **Multi-point** -- PSLQ finds relations among f at different x-values, but always uses as many coefficients as data points (no compression).\n\n8. **Fourier analysis** -- In log-space, dominant frequency omega = 14.01, matching the first zeta zero gamma_1 = 14.1347. Confirms zeta-zero dominance.\n\n**Critical finding from cross-validation:** ALL single-point PSLQ/polynomial relations are **spurious**. They hold only at the fitted x-value and fail with residuals of 10^3 to 10^6 at other x-values. This is expected: with N basis functions and 1 equation, PSLQ always finds a relation (underdetermined system). The tiny residuals (~10^{-37}) merely reflect 50-digit arithmetic precision.\n\n**Conclusion:** f(x) = pi(x) - R(x) satisfies no algebraic, polynomial, recurrence, modular, functional, or linear identity involving elementary/classical functions. This further confirms the information-theoretic barrier: the oscillatory residual encodes zeta-zero phases that are incompressible. Added to `status/CLOSED_PATHS.md`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":331,"cache_read_input_tokens":52305,"output_tokens":769,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":331},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjR2akJ2RUGNdAUAFcBg","type":"assistant","uuid":"f4e5baf4-ff26-4a2d-b064-1c74c37329f1","timestamp":"2026-04-04T21:09:02.179Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"a7d53bb6-087f-4e7d-81de-1d8a45f40cf3","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"main","slug":"sparkling-chasing-pascal"}
    
