Strong result from the unbalanced agent. **Universal formula**: rank = 2^{min(k,N-k)-1}+2 for all partitions with min(k,N-k) >= 3. The rank depends ONLY on the size of the smaller side and stabilizes once N >= 2k. No polynomial-rank partition exists. The sqrt(x) barrier is intrinsic to pi(x) regardless of how you split the input bits.

