Very interesting 3-party NOF result, but I need to interpret it carefully:

- **Best (1,1,N-2) split**: NOF complexity = O(1) — but this is **trivially true for ALL functions** (any function has cut rank ≤ 4 with such extreme splits)
- **Balanced (N/3, N/3, N/3) split**: cut rank follows 2^{N/3-1}+2 pattern — still exponential
- The 3-party complexity is Theta(N/3), consistent with pi(x) potentially being in ACC^0/TC^0 but not proving it

