The Kt agent's interpretation is worth highlighting — it decomposes delta(n) into:
1. **Smooth trend** (autocorr 0.998) — trackable incrementally but not computable from scratch
2. **Random residual** (std ~10.5, ~3-4 bits/step) — the true barrier, accumulating to ~0.5·log₂(n) unpredictable bits

This is the information barrier in its most granular empirical form: you can predict delta(n) from delta(n-1) to within ±10.5, but you can't predict it from scratch without O(sqrt(x)) work. The ~520 approaches tested across 19 sessions all converge to this same wall.
